{"actual":"Rejected with NexusError as expected, even under a self-consistent digest patch.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"APPARATUS","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"./nexus audit-check correctly detects a route pack built against the wrong baseline commit, even when the route pack's own digest is patched into TARGET.json to be self-consistent.","classification":"OBSERVATION","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["In an isolated clone, a route pack was rebuilt from a task file whose baseline_ref pointed to the parent commit (ab6a56e...) instead of target_commit. The forged pack replaced RTE-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND-AUDIT.zip and TARGET.json.route_pack.sha256 was updated to match it. ./nexus audit-check then reported: NEXUS ERROR: Audit route baseline is ambiguously bound to a different target commit. Exit code 2."],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py:check_audit","system/nexus_lab/route.py:verify_manifest_pack"],"expected":"Ambiguous route/target binding is a failure condition per EXTERNAL_WITNESS_ARCHITECTURE.md.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py","system/nexus_lab/route.py","operations/tasks/TSK-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND-AUDIT.json"],"limitations":["Tested only in an isolated temporary clone; the source repository was never modified.","This binding is stronger than the raw-archive-digest binding in AUDOBS-0003 because verify_manifest_pack independently re-derives baseline_commit from ROUTE.json rather than trusting only a co-located digest declaration; the archive case (AUDOBS-0003) lacks an equivalent independent re-derivation."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0006","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"","record_hash":"","reproduction":["git clone <repo> /tmp/clone","copy operations/tasks/TSK-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND-AUDIT.json, set baseline_ref to the parent commit and a new route_id","./nexus --root /tmp/clone route <modified task>","copy the resulting zip over operations/audits/AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND/RTE-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND-AUDIT.zip, recompute its sha256, and patch TARGET.json.route_pack.sha256 to match","./nexus --root /tmp/clone audit-check --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"INFO","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"All eight attempted traversal/unsafe-path variants were rejected with NexusError before any file was written outside the intended tree.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"ROUTING","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"Path traversal, absolute-path, .git-inclusion, and unsafe-zip-member attempts are uniformly rejected across route building, pack verification, and observation ingestion.","classification":"OBSERVATION","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["Task with include_paths=['../../../../etc/passwd'] -> NEXUS ERROR: Unsafe repository path: '../../../../etc/passwd'","Task with include_paths=['/etc/passwd'] -> NEXUS ERROR: Unsafe repository path: '/etc/passwd'","Task with include_paths=['.git/config'] -> NEXUS ERROR: The .git directory cannot be routed or packaged.","Task with output_contract.schema_path='../../../../etc/passwd' -> NEXUS ERROR: Unsafe repository path","A hand-crafted zip containing a member named '../evil.txt' fed to verify_manifest_pack -> NEXUS ERROR: Unsafe repository path: '../evil.txt'","Observation with observation_id='../../../etc/passwd' fed to audit-ingest --check-only -> NEXUS ERROR: Unsafe observation_id"],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/util.py:validate_relative_path","system/nexus_lab/util.py:validate_identifier","system/nexus_lab/route.py:_expand_at_commit","system/nexus_lab/route.py:verify_manifest_pack"],"expected":"CLAUDE_AUDIT_GUIDE.md requires attempting route path traversal and undeclared-file inclusion.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/util.py","system/nexus_lab/route.py","system/nexus_lab/audit.py"],"limitations":["Only the specific traversal patterns tested were exercised (../, absolute path, .git member, crafted zip member, malformed observation_id); other encodings (URL-encoded, unicode look-alikes, NTFS-style paths) were not tested and this repository is Linux/POSIX-oriented so some of those classes may not apply."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0007","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"","record_hash":"","reproduction":["Construct task JSON variants with traversal/absolute/.git paths and run ./nexus route <task> in an isolated clone","Construct a zip with a '../' member name and call verify_manifest_pack() directly","Construct an observation JSON with a traversal observation_id and run ./nexus audit-ingest --check-only"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"INFO","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"All nine variants were rejected with a specific, correct NexusError and non-zero exit code; none silently passed or partially applied.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"APPARATUS","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"Malformed and self-promoting audit observations are uniformly rejected by check-only validation: status_authority override, undeclared extra keys, mismatched target_commit, mismatched target_archive_sha256, invalid classification value, forged non-matching record_hash, forged non-matching previous_record_hash, mismatched audit_id, and empty/whitespace-only claim were each tested individually.","classification":"OBSERVATION","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["status_authority='ACCEPTED' -> NEXUS ERROR: Audit observations must declare status_authority NONE.","extra key 'approved':true -> NEXUS ERROR: Observation has undeclared keys: approved","target_commit='0'*40 -> NEXUS ERROR: Observation target commit does not match TARGET.json.","target_archive_sha256='0'*64 -> NEXUS ERROR: Observation target archive digest does not match TARGET.json.","classification='CONFIRMED_DEFECT' -> NEXUS ERROR: Invalid observation classification.","record_hash='deadbeef'*8 -> NEXUS ERROR: Observation record_hash is invalid; computed <correct-hash>.","previous_record_hash='deadbeef'*8 -> NEXUS ERROR: Observation previous_record_hash does not match ledger head ''.","audit_id='AUD-R001-CLAUDE-BLIND' while targeting AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND -> NEXUS ERROR: Observation audit_id does not match the selected audit.","claim='   ' -> NEXUS ERROR: Observation claim must be one non-empty claim."],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py:validate_observation"],"expected":"CLAUDE_AUDIT_GUIDE.md requires submitting malformed, mismatched and self-promoting observations in check-only mode.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py"],"limitations":["Only the nine listed mutations were tested; the field-level validator was not exhaustively fuzzed (e.g. wrong types for list fields, non-dict auditor field with extra nested keys, non-UTF8 content)."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0008","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"","record_hash":"","reproduction":["In an isolated clone, construct nine observation-JSON variants from OBSERVATION_TEMPLATE.json, each with exactly one field mutated as listed, and run ./nexus audit-ingest --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND --check-only <file> for each"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"INFO","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"All four sub-cases behaved as documented.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"APPARATUS","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"In a clean isolated clone, legitimate observation append, duplicate-observation_id rejection, and ledger hash-chain tamper detection (both in-place content edit and line-reorder) all function correctly.","classification":"OBSERVATION","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["First real (non-check-only) ingest of a valid observation succeeded and ./nexus audit-check reported status PASS with observation_count 1.","Re-ingesting the identical observation_id -> NEXUS ERROR: Duplicate observation_id: AUDOBS-CLEAN-0001.","Editing the 'claim' field of the already-appended ledger line in place (leaving record_hash untouched) -> NEXUS ERROR: Audit ledger record hash mismatch on line 1.","Appending a second legitimate observation, then swapping the order of the two ledger lines -> NEXUS ERROR: Audit ledger chain break on line 1."],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py:ingest_observation","system/nexus_lab/audit.py:check_audit"],"expected":"constitution/AUDIT.md requires append-only, hash-chained observation records where silence is not a pass and inability to detect tampering would be a defect.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py"],"limitations":["An earlier attempt at this same test sequence in a different, heavily-reused temporary clone (which had several unrelated attack mutations applied and only partially reverted) produced a spurious hash-mismatch error before any tampering was applied. That result was not reproducible in a freshly cloned, single-purpose environment and is attributed to auditor test-harness contamination (leftover unreverted route-pack/TARGET.json edits from a prior attack in the same clone), not a tool defect. This is disclosed for transparency; it is not being reported as a finding against the tool."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0009","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"","record_hash":"","reproduction":["git clone <repo> /tmp/clone3","./nexus --root /tmp/clone3 audit-ingest --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND <valid-observation.json>","./nexus --root /tmp/clone3 audit-check --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","re-run the same ingest to observe duplicate rejection","edit ledger line 1's claim text in place and re-run audit-check","reset, ingest two observations, swap ledger line order, re-run audit-check"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"INFO","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"The rebuild is only self-consistent within one environment's zlib build; it does not reproduce the specific checked-in canonical bytes when the zlib implementation differs, even though the underlying content is provably identical (matching payload manifest hash). No unit test or CI step rebuilds-and-compares against the actual checked-in snapshots/canonical or audit target archive; test_snapshot.py only compares two builds performed within the same test process.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"ARCHIVE","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"DEMO-002's claim that 'Same committed tree and profile produce byte-identical ZIPs' holds only within a fixed toolchain/environment. In this audit environment (Python 3.14.6, zlib-ng 1.3.1), running `./nexus freeze --ref baseline-001 --snapshot-id NEXUS-LAB-R001-BASELINE-001 --profile full-private-git` twice back-to-back produced byte-identical output both times (self-consistent), but neither run reproduced the byte-for-byte content of the checked-in canonical/target archive, despite the decompressed payload and its manifest hash matching exactly.","classification":"SUSPECTED_DEFECT","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["./nexus freeze --ref baseline-001 --snapshot-id NEXUS-LAB-R001-BASELINE-001 --profile full-private-git run twice in this environment produced archive_sha256=3c673e6c... both times (identical to each other).","The checked-in canonical archive at snapshots/canonical/NEXUS_LAB_R001_BASELINE_001.zip has archive_sha256=33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603, which does not match this environment's rebuild.","Extracting both archives showed identical file lists, identical _nexus/PAYLOAD_MANIFEST.sha256 content, and identical _nexus/SNAPSHOT_METADATA.json content (byte-for-byte, via diff); only the outer ZIP container bytes differ, with the first divergent bytes appearing inside a DEFLATE-compressed member around offset ~9975.","python3 -c 'import zlib; print(zlib.ZLIB_RUNTIME_VERSION)' reported '1.3.1.zlib-ng' in this environment, a different DEFLATE implementation than stock zlib, which is known to produce different (but equally valid) compressed output for identical input at the same compression level."],"exact_location":["docs/DEMONSTRATION.md:DEMO-002","tests/test_snapshot.py:test_same_commit_produces_byte_identical_snapshot","system/nexus_lab/snapshot.py:_write_zip"],"expected":"DEMO-002 states the reproducibility property without scoping it to a fixed toolchain; a reader could take 'byte-identical' to mean reproducible by any auditor rebuilding from the same tagged commit.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["docs/DEMONSTRATION.md","tests/test_snapshot.py","system/nexus_lab/snapshot.py",".github/workflows/nexus-audit.yml"],"limitations":["This finding is about the outer ZIP container's byte-identity claim, not about content integrity; verify_snapshot()'s internal manifest checks (which do not depend on exact compressed bytes) still correctly validate the canonical archive's content. The root cause (zlib-ng vs stock zlib) is inferred from indirect evidence (matching payload content, differing compressed bytes, a non-default zlib build present in this sandbox) rather than directly proven by building the canonical archive under a stock-zlib environment for a side-by-side comparison, which this environment does not support."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0010","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"Either (a) scope DEMO-002's claim explicitly to 'within the pinned toolchain used for CI/release', or (b) make byte-identity independent of the DEFLATE implementation, e.g. by storing/verifying only the payload and package manifests (content hashes) as the portable determinism guarantee and treating exact compressed bytes as an implementation detail.","record_hash":"","reproduction":["./nexus freeze --ref baseline-001 --snapshot-id NEXUS-LAB-R001-BASELINE-001 --output /tmp/rebuild.zip --profile full-private-git","sha256sum /tmp/rebuild.zip snapshots/canonical/NEXUS_LAB_R001_BASELINE_001.zip","unzip both and diff the extracted _nexus/*.json and _nexus/*.sha256 files to confirm content equivalence despite the outer-archive digest mismatch"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"MEDIUM","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"Add a CI or test step that runs ./nexus freeze against the actual tagged baseline-001 commit and asserts the output equals the checked-in snapshots/canonical/*.zip and operations/audits/*/target/*.zip byte-for-byte (not just a same-process two-build comparison), and pin/declare the zlib implementation and version used to build canonical artifacts.","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
